Each of those dictionaries represents an object, with the keys corresponding to the attribute names of model objects.

>>> Blog.objects.filter(name__startswith='Beatles')
<QuerySet [<Blog: Beatles Blog>]>

<QuerySet [{'id': 1, 'name': 'Beatles Blog', 'tagline': 'All the latest Beatles news.'}]>

"DirectX's assembler's language" is just language, which will be translated to byte-code, which in turn will be translated by video-accelerator's driver in code which more understandable for video-accelerator and then will be executed.
